{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483652277,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdcd244001fTt9CpsYOHDhWn","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdcc6fc001v5dD7T26PPHtG4","type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me analyze what needs to be done:\n\n1. **Handle agents that finish while monitor is closed** — detect completion on next monitor open and update state/UI. This is already handled by `resume.ts`'s triage logic (checking PID alive, verifying builds, etc.). But we need to verify the TUI command loop handles this correctly.\n\n2. **Show a 'running wave detected' indicator in the Task Browser** — The `TaskBrowser` has `setHasRunningWave()` and the header/status bar support it, but the `showBrowser()` function in `tui.ts` line 1004 hardcodes `onSwitchToMonitor: undefined`. We need to wire it up.\n\n3. **Edge cases: all agents finish while closed, mixed success/failure while closed** — Resume logic handles these, but we should ensure the TUI loop properly transitions.\n\nLet me also check the quit behavior in the TUI — does pressing Q in the wave monitor actually kill agents? This is the core of \"quit should not stop running agents\":","time":{"start":1773483652277,"end":1773483652277}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483652285,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdcef79001TfTxKjc4Df3woU","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdcc6fc001v5dD7T26PPHtG4","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01PxKrB3NFvMpCgeUWtorDrM","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts","offset":1419},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1419: // cleanup is needed when the parent exits. The `launchInteractive()` function\n1420: // in launcher.ts returns `process: null as any` (no ChildProcess handle).\n1421: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1422: \n1423: async function launchWaveInteractive(\n1424:   projectRoot: string,\n1425:   state: WaveState,\n1426:   features: Feature[],\n1427:   opts: LaunchCommandOptions,\n1428:   agentResolutions?: Map<string, AgentResolution>,\n1429:   questContext?: QuestPromptContext,\n1430:   hitlMode?: string\n1431: ): Promise<void> {\n1432:   const { config, model } = opts;\n1433:   const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n1434:   const featureMap = new Map(features.map((f) => [f.id, f]));\n1435: \n1436:   // Show dashboard immediately\n1437:   if (fmt === \"text\") printDashboard(state);\n1438: \n1439:   // Launch initial batch — parallelize setup\n1440:   const tolaunch = queuedAgents(state).slice(0, opts.maxConcurrent);\n1441:   if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`Setting up ${tolaunch.length} agent(s) in parallel...\\n`);\n1442: \n1443:   await Promise.all(\n1444:     tolaunch.map(async (agent) => {\n1445:       updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n1446:         status: \"installing\",\n1447:         started_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n1448:         activity: \"setting up worktree...\",\n1449:       });\n1450:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n1451: \n1452:       try {\n1453:         if (worktreeReady(agent.worktree)) {\n1454:           wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"worktree already exists, skipping setup\");\n1455:         } else {\n1456:           await createWorktree(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, state.base_branch, config);\n1457:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, { activity: \"installing deps...\" });\n1458:           await installDeps(agent.worktree, agent.feature_id, config);\n1459:         }\n1460: \n1461:         const prompt = generatePrompt(\n1462:           featureMap.get(agent.feature_id)!,\n1463:           state.base_branch,\n1464:           config,\n1465:           questContext,\n1466:           hitlMode as QuestHitlMode | undefined\n1467:         );\n1468: \n1469:         // Write specialized agent to worktree if applicable\n1470:         const resolution = agentResolutions?.get(agent.feature_id);\n1471:         const agentName = agent.agent_name ?? undefined;\n1472:         if (resolution && isSpecializedAgent(resolution)) {\n1473:           try {\n1474:             const patchedContent = patchImportedAgent(resolution.rawContent, config, projectRoot);\n1475:             writeAgentToWorktree(agent.worktree, resolution.name, patchedContent);\n1476:             wtLog(agent.feature_id, `wrote specialized agent: ${resolution.name}`);\n1477:           } catch (err: any) {\n1478:             wtLog(agent.feature_id, `WARN: failed to write specialized agent, using generalist: ${err.message}`);\n1479:           }\n1480:         }\n1481: \n1482:         wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"launching interactive session...\");\n1483:         const result = launchInteractive({\n1484:           worktreePath: agent.worktree,\n1485:           featureId: agent.feature_id,\n1486:           prompt,\n1487:           model,\n1488:           interactive: true,\n1489:           config,\n1490:           agentName,\n1491:         });\n1492: \n1493:         const muxName = getMultiplexerName(config);\n1494:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n1495:           status: \"running\",\n1496:           pid: result.pid,\n1497:           activity: `${muxName} session active`,\n1498:         });\n1499:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n1500:         wtLog(agent.feature_id, `${muxName} session: ${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-${agent.feature_id}`);\n1501:       } catch (err: any) {\n1502:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n1503:           status: \"failed\",\n1504:           error: err.message,\n1505:           activity: null,\n1506:           completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n1507:         });\n1508:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n1509:         wtLog(agent.feature_id, `SETUP FAILED: ${err.message.split(\"\\n\")[0]}`);\n1510:       }\n1511:     })\n1512:   );\n1513: \n1514:   const mux = detectMultiplexer(config.agent.multiplexer);\n1515:   const muxName = getMultiplexerName(config);\n1516:   if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1517:     console.log(\"\\nInteractive sessions launched. Use these commands:\");\n1518:     console.log(`  ${muxAttachCommand(mux, `${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-<feature-id>`)}   # attach to a session`);\n1519:     console.log(`  ${muxListCommand(mux)}${\" \".repeat(Math.max(1, 54 - muxListCommand(mux).length))}# list sessions`);\n1520:     console.log(\"  woco status                                             # check status\");\n1521:     console.log(\"  woco verify                                             # verify builds\");\n1522:     console.log(\"  woco merge                                              # merge verified\");\n1523:     console.log(\"  woco cleanup                                            # remove worktrees\");\n1524: \n1525:     printDashboard(state);\n1526:   }\n1527: }\n1528: \n1529: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1530: // Main Command\n1531: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1532: \n1533: export async function cmdLaunch(opts: LaunchCommandOptions): Promise<void> {\n1534:   const { projectRoot } = opts;\n1535:   let { config } = opts;\n1536:   const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n1537: \n1538:   if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(\"\\n--- wombo-combo: Launch ---\\n\");\n1539: \n1540:   // Ensure agent definition exists — reinstall from template if missing\n1541:   ensureAgentDefinition(projectRoot, config, opts.agent);\n1542: \n1543:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1544:   // Quest resolution — if --quest was specified, scope the wave to that quest\n1545:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1546:   let questContext: QuestPromptContext | undefined;\n1547:   let questId: string | null = opts.questId ?? null;\n1548: \n1549:   if (questId) {\n1550:     const quest = loadQuest(projectRoot, questId);\n1551:     if (!quest) {\n1552:       outputError(fmt, `Quest \"${questId}\" not found. Use 'woco quest list' to see available quests.`);\n1553:       return; // unreachable\n1554:     }\n1555: \n1556:     if (quest.status !== \"active\") {\n1557:       outputError(fmt, `Quest \"${questId}\" is in status \"${quest.status}\" — only active quests can be launched. Use 'woco quest activate ${questId}' first.`);\n1558:       return; // unreachable\n1559:     }\n1560: \n1561:     // Ensure the quest branch exists (create from baseBranch if needed)\n1562:     if (!questBranchExists(projectRoot, questId)) {\n1563:       if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`Creating quest branch \"${quest.branch}\" from \"${quest.baseBranch}\"...`);\n1564:       createQuestBranch(projectRoot, questId, quest.baseBranch);\n1565:     }\n1566: \n1567:     // Override baseBranch — task branches will fork from the quest branch\n1568:     opts.baseBranch = quest.branch;\n1569:     if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1570:       console.log(`Quest: ${quest.title} (${questId})`);\n1571:       console.log(`  Base branch overridden to: ${quest.branch}`);\n1572:     }\n1573: \n1574:     // Apply quest config overrides (layered on top of project config)\n1575:     config = resolveQuestConfig(config, quest);\n1576: \n1577:     // Build quest prompt context for agent prompts\n1578:     const knowledge = loadQuestKnowledge(projectRoot, questId);\n1579:     questContext = {\n1580:       questId: quest.id,\n1581:       goal: quest.goal,\n1582:       addedConstraints: quest.constraints.add ?? [],\n1583:       addedForbidden: quest.constraints.ban ?? [],\n1584:       knowledge,\n1585:     };\n1586: \n1587:     if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1588:       const constraintCount = questContext.addedConstraints.length + questContext.addedForbidden.length;\n1589:       if (constraintCount > 0) {\n1590:         console.log(`  Quest constraints: ${questContext.addedConstraints.length} added, ${questContext.addedForbidden.length} banned`);\n1591:       }\n1592:       if (knowledge) {\n1593:         console.log(`  Quest knowledge: loaded (${knowledge.length} bytes)`);\n1594:       }\n1595:       console.log(\"\");\n1596:     }\n1597:   }\n1598: \n1599:   // Extract HITL mode from quest (defaults to undefined / yolo for non-quest waves)\n1600:   const hitlMode = questId ? loadQuest(projectRoot, questId)?.hitlMode : undefined;\n1601: \n1602:   // Ensure portless proxy is running (if enabled) to prevent port collisions\n1603:   if (config.portless.enabled) {\n1604:     if (isPortlessAvailable(config)) {\n1605:       const proxyOk = ensureProxyRunning(config);\n1606:       if (!proxyOk && fmt === \"text\") {\n1607:         console.warn(\n1608:           \"\\x1b[33m[portless]\\x1b[0m proxy could not be started — agents may encounter port collisions\"\n1609:         );\n1610:       }\n1611:     } else if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1612:       console.warn(\n1613:         \"\\x1b[33m[portless]\\x1b[0m enabled but not installed. Install with: npm install -g portless\"\n1614:       );\n1615:       console.warn(\n1616:         \"  Agents will run without portless — concurrent dev servers may have port collisions.\\n\"\n1617:       );\n1618:     }\n1619:   }\n1620: \n1621:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1622:   // Validate that the configured baseBranch exists as a local branch\n1623:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1624:   if (!branchExists(projectRoot, opts.baseBranch)) {\n1625:     const msg = `Base branch \"${opts.baseBranch}\" does not exist as a local branch. ` +\n1626:       `Create it first (e.g. \"git checkout -b ${opts.baseBranch}\") or specify ` +\n1627:       `a different branch with --base-branch.`;\n1628:     outputError(fmt, msg);\n1629:   }\n1630: \n1631:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1632:   // Check for existing wave state — don't overwrite work in progress\n1633:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1634:   const existingState = loadState(projectRoot);\n1635:   if (existingState) {\n1636:     const merged = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"merged\");\n1637:     const verified = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"verified\");\n1638:     const completed = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"completed\");\n1639:     const running = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"running\");\n1640:     const queued = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"queued\");\n1641:     const failed = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"failed\");\n1642: \n1643:     const hasWork = merged.length > 0 || verified.length > 0 || completed.length > 0 || running.length > 0;\n1644: \n1645:     if (hasWork) {\n1646:       if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1647:         console.log(`Existing wave found: ${existingState.wave_id}`);\n1648:         console.log(`  ${merged.length} merged, ${verified.length} verified, ${completed.length} completed, ${running.length} running, ${queued.length} queued, ${failed.length} failed`);\n1649:       }\n1650: \n1651:       // Finalize any merged agents by marking their features as done\n1652:       const finalizedIds: string[] = [];\n1653:       if (merged.length > 0) {\n1654:         if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(\"\\nFinalizing merged tasks in tasks file...\");\n1655:         for (const agent of merged) {\n1656:           markFeatureDone(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, config, existingState.base_branch, fmt);\n1657:           finalizedIds.push(agent.feature_id);\n1658:           // Clean up worktree and branch (already merged, safe to delete)\n1659:           try {\n1660:             removeWorktree(projectRoot, agent.worktree, true);\n1661:             if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: marked done, worktree removed`);\n1662:           } catch {\n1663:             if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: marked done (worktree already cleaned)`);\n1664:           }\n1665:         }\n1666:       }\n1667: \n1668:       // Strip finalized task IDs from explicit selection so we don't\n1669:       // try to re-launch tasks that were just marked done\n1670:       if (finalizedIds.length > 0 && opts.features?.length) {\n1671:         const finalizedSet = new Set(finalizedIds);\n1672:         opts.features = opts.features.filter((id) => !finalizedSet.has(id));\n1673:       }\n1674: \n1675:       // Verified agents: build passed but NOT merged — do NOT mark done.\n1676:       // Leave them for 'woco resume' to attempt the merge.\n1677:       if (verified.length > 0) {\n1678:         for (const agent of verified) {\n1679:           if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: verified (not yet merged) — use 'woco resume' to merge`);\n1680:         }\n1681:       }\n1682: \n1683:       const activeCount = running.length + completed.length + queued.length;\n1684:       if (activeCount > 0) {\n1685:         outputError(fmt, `Wave ${existingState.wave_id} has ${activeCount} unfinished agent(s). Use 'woco resume' to continue the existing wave, or 'woco cleanup' to clear it before starting a new one.`);\n1686:       }\n1687: \n1688:       // All agents are in terminal states (merged/verified/failed) — safe to start fresh\n1689:       if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(\"\\nAll agents in previous wave are finished. Starting fresh wave.\\n\");\n1690:     }\n1691:   }\n1692: \n1693:   // Load features\n1694:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n1695: \n1696:   // Build selection options\n1697:   const selOpts: SelectionOptions = {};\n1698:   if (opts.topPriority) selOpts.topPriority = opts.topPriority;\n1699:   if (opts.quickestWins) selOpts.quickestWins = opts.quickestWins;\n1700:   if (opts.priority) selOpts.priority = opts.priority;\n1701:   if (opts.difficulty) selOpts.difficulty = opts.difficulty;\n1702:   if (opts.features) selOpts.taskIds = opts.features;\n1703:   if (opts.allReady) selOpts.allReady = true;\n1704: \n1705:   // Select features\n1706:   let selected = selectFeatures(data, selOpts);\n1707: \n1708:   if (selected.length === 0) {\n1709:     // Build a context-aware message based on which flags were passed\n1710:     const activeFilters: string[] = [];\n1711:     if (opts.allReady) activeFilters.push(\"--all-ready\");\n1712:     if (opts.topPriority) activeFilters.push(`--top-priority ${opts.topPriority}`);\n1713:     if (opts.quickestWins) activeFilters.push(`--quickest-wins ${opts.quickestWins}`);\n1714:     if (opts.priority) activeFilters.push(`--priority ${opts.priority}`);\n1715:     if (opts.difficulty) activeFilters.push(`--difficulty ${opts.difficulty}`);\n1716:     if (opts.features?.length) activeFilters.push(`--tasks ${opts.features.join(\",\")}`);\n1717: \n1718:     let msg: string;\n1719:     if (opts.allReady && activeFilters.length === 1) {\n1720:       msg = \"No launchable tasks found (all tasks are done, cancelled, or have unmet dependencies).\";\n1721:     } else if (activeFilters.length > 0) {\n1722:       msg = `No tasks matched the current filters: ${activeFilters.join(\", \")}.`;\n1723:     } else {\n1724:       msg = \"No launchable tasks found.\";\n1725:     }\n1726: \n1727:     // Throw instead of outputError so TUI callers can catch gracefully.\n1728:     // CLI callers catch this in the command handler (index.ts).\n1729:     throw new Error(msg);\n1730:   }\n1731: \n1732:   // Apply quest constraints to selected tasks (add/ban layered on each task)\n1733:   if (questId && questContext) {\n1734:     const quest = loadQuest(projectRoot, questId)!;\n1735:     selected = selected.map((f) => applyQuestConstraintsToTask(f, quest));\n1736:   }\n1737: \n1738:   // Show selection\n1739:   if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1740:     printFeatureSelection(\n1741:       selected.map((f) => ({\n1742:         id: f.id,\n1743:         title: f.title,\n1744:         priority: f.priority,\n1745:         difficulty: f.difficulty,\n1746:         effort: f.effort,\n1747:       }))\n1748:     );\n1749:   }\n1750: \n1751:   // Check per-task agent definitions exist\n1752:   if (!opts.agent) {\n1753:     const taskAgents = new Set(\n1754:       selected.map((f) => f.agent).filter((a): a is string => !!a)\n1755:     );\n1756:     for (const agentName of taskAgents) {\n1757:       ensureAgentDefinition(projectRoot, config, agentName);\n1758:     }\n1759:   }\n1760: \n1761:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1762:   // Dependency graph analysis\n1763:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1764:   const depGraph = buildDepGraph(selected, data.tasks);\n1765:   let schedulePlan: SchedulePlan | null = null;\n1766: \n1767:   // Check if any features actually have dependencies within the selected set\n1768:   const hasDeps = selected.some(\n1769:     (f) => f.depends_on.some((d) => selected.find((s) => s.id === d))\n1770:   );\n1771: \n1772:   if (hasDeps) {\n1773:     // Validate graph — throws on cycles or dangling deps\n1774:     try {\n1775:       validateDepGraph(depGraph);\n1776:     } catch (err: any) {\n1777:       outputError(fmt, `${err.message}\\nFix dependency issues before launching.`);\n1778:     }\n1779: \n1780:     // Build scheduling plan\n1781:     schedulePlan = buildSchedulePlan(depGraph);\n1782:     if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`\\n${formatSchedulePlan(schedulePlan)}\\n`);\n1783:   }\n1784: \n1785:   if (opts.dryRun) {\n1786:     const dryRunResult = {\n1787:       dry_run: true,\n1788:       base_branch: opts.baseBranch,\n1789:       max_concurrent: opts.maxConcurrent,\n1790:       model: opts.model ?? null,\n1791:       interactive: opts.interactive,\n1792:       selected: selected.map((f) => ({\n1793:         id: f.id,\n1794:         title: f.title,\n1795:         priority: f.priority,\n1796:         difficulty: f.difficulty,\n1797:         effort: f.effort,\n1798:       })),\n1799:       schedule_plan: schedulePlan ? {\n1800:         streams: schedulePlan.streams.map((s) => s.featureIds),\n1801:         merge_gates: schedulePlan.mergeGates.map((g) => ({\n1802:           feature_id: g.featureId,\n1803:           wait_for: g.waitFor,\n1804:         })),\n1805:         topological_order: schedulePlan.topologicalOrder,\n1806:       } : null,\n1807:     };\n1808: \n1809:     output(fmt, dryRunResult, () => {\n1810:       console.log(\"Dry run — not launching agents.\");\n1811:     }, () => {\n1812:       console.log(renderLaunchDryRun(dryRunResult));\n1813:     });\n1814:     return;\n1815:   }\n1816: \n1817:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1818:   // Agent registry: resolve specialized agents for tasks with agent_type\n1819:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1820:   let agentResolutions: Map<string, AgentResolution> | undefined;\n1821: \n1822:   if (config.agentRegistry.mode !== \"disabled\") {\n1823:     const tasksWithAgentType = selected.filter((t) => t.agent_type);\n1824:     if (tasksWithAgentType.length > 0) {\n1825:       if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`\\nResolving ${tasksWithAgentType.length} specialized agent(s) from registry...`);\n1826:       agentResolutions = await prepareAgentDefinitions(selected, config, projectRoot);\n1827: \n1828:       const specialized = [...agentResolutions.values()].filter(isSpecializedAgent);\n1829:       const cached = specialized.filter((r) => r.fromCache);\n1830:       if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1831:         console.log(\n1832:           `  ${specialized.length} specialized (${cached.length} cached, ${specialized.length - cached.length} fetched), ` +\n1833:           `${selected.length - specialized.length} generalist`\n1834:         );\n1835:       }\n1836:     }\n1837:   }\n1838: \n1839:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1840:   // Preflight confirmation\n1841:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1842:   if (agentResolutions && agentResolutions.size > 0) {\n1843:     const isTTY = process.stdout.isTTY && process.stdin.isTTY;\n1844:     const preflight = isTTY && !opts.noTui\n1845:       ? await tuiPreflightConfirm(selected, agentResolutions, config)\n1846:       : await consolePreflightConfirm(selected, agentResolutions, config);\n1847: \n1848:     if (!preflight.proceed) {\n1849:       outputMessage(fmt, \"Launch cancelled.\");\n1850:       return;\n1851:     }\n1852: \n1853:     // Apply user's changes (rejected agents, mode changes)\n1854:     agentResolutions = preflight.agents;\n1855:   }\n1856: \n1857:   // Create wave state\n1858:   const state = createWaveState({\n1859:     baseBranch: opts.baseBranch,\n1860:     maxConcurrent: opts.maxConcurrent,\n1861:     model: opts.model ?? null,\n1862:     interactive: opts.interactive,\n1863:     questId,\n1864:   });\n1865: \n1866:   // Store serialized schedule plan in wave state\n1867:   if (schedulePlan) {\n1868:     state.schedule_plan = {\n1869:       streams: schedulePlan.streams.map((s) => s.featureIds),\n1870:       merge_gates: schedulePlan.mergeGates.map((g) => ({\n1871:         feature_id: g.featureId,\n1872:         wait_for: g.waitFor,\n1873:       })),\n1874:       topological_order: schedulePlan.topologicalOrder,\n1875:     };\n1876:   }\n1877: \n1878:   // Create agent entries for all selected features\n1879:   const selectedIds = new Set(selected.map((f) => f.id));\n1880: \n1881:   // Build a map from feature ID → shared worktree path for chain reuse.\n1882:   // All features in the same chain share the worktree of the chain's first feature.\n1883:   const chainWorktreeMap = new Map<string, string>();\n1884:   if (schedulePlan) {\n1885:     for (const stream of schedulePlan.streams) {\n1886:       if (stream.featureIds.length > 1) {\n1887:         // All features in this chain share the first feature's worktree\n1888:         const sharedWtPath = worktreePath(projectRoot, stream.featureIds[0], config);\n1889:         for (const featureId of stream.featureIds) {\n1890:           chainWorktreeMap.set(featureId, sharedWtPath);\n1891:         }\n1892:       }\n1893:     }\n1894:   }\n1895: \n1896:   for (const feature of selected) {\n1897:     const branch = featureBranchName(feature.id, config);\n1898:     // Use shared worktree path for chain members, or individual path otherwise\n1899:     const wtPath = chainWorktreeMap.get(feature.id) ?? worktreePath(projectRoot, feature.id, config);\n1900:     const agent = createAgentState(feature.id, branch, wtPath, opts.maxRetries);\n1901: \n1902:     // Set effort estimate from feature spec\n1903:     const effortMinutes = parseDurationMinutes(feature.effort);\n1904:     agent.effort_estimate_ms = effortMinutes === Infinity ? null : effortMinutes * 60 * 1000;\n1905: \n1906:     // Populate dependency fields from the graph\n1907:     const graphNode = depGraph.nodes.get(feature.id);\n1908:     if (graphNode) {\n1909:       // Only track internal deps (within the selected set)\n1910:       agent.depends_on = graphNode.dependsOn.filter((d) => selectedIds.has(d));\n1911:       agent.depended_on_by = graphNode.dependedOnBy.filter((d) => selectedIds.has(d));\n1912:     }\n1913: \n1914:     // Set stream index\n1915:     if (schedulePlan) {\n1916:       agent.stream_index = getStreamForFeature(schedulePlan, feature.id);\n1917:     }\n1918: \n1919:     // Set specialized agent info from resolution\n1920:     const resolution = agentResolutions?.get(feature.id);\n1921:     if (resolution && isSpecializedAgent(resolution)) {\n1922:       agent.agent_name = resolution.name;\n1923:       agent.agent_type = resolution.agentType;\n1924:     }\n1925: \n1926:     // Per-task local agent override: CLI --agent flag takes precedence,\n1927:     // then task-level `agent` field, then registry resolution (above).\n1928:     // This is for local agent definitions in .opencode/agents/<name>.md.\n1929:     const localAgent = opts.agent ?? feature.agent;\n1930:     if (localAgent && !agent.agent_name) {\n1931:       // Only set if not already resolved from the external registry\n1932:       agent.agent_name = localAgent;\n1933:     } else if (opts.agent) {\n1934:       // CLI --agent flag overrides even registry agents\n1935:       agent.agent_name = opts.agent;\n1936:     }\n1937: \n1938:     state.agents.push(agent);\n1939:   }\n1940: \n1941:   saveState(projectRoot, state);\n1942:   if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`Wave ${state.wave_id} created with ${selected.length} agents.`);\n1943: \n1944:   // Launch agents up to max_concurrent\n1945:   if (opts.interactive) {\n1946:     await launchWaveInteractive(projectRoot, state, selected, opts, agentResolutions, questContext, hitlMode);\n1947:   } else {\n1948:     await launchWaveHeadless(projectRoot, state, selected, opts, agentResolutions, questContext, hitlMode);\n1949:   }\n1950: }\n\n(End of file - total 1950 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/launch.ts","metadata":{"preview":"// cleanup is needed when the parent exits. The `launchInteractive()` function\n// in launcher.ts returns `process: null as any` (no ChildProcess handle).\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nasync function launchWaveInteractive(\n  projectRoot: string,\n  state: WaveState,\n  features: Feature[],\n  opts: LaunchCommandOptions,\n  agentResolutions?: Map<string, AgentResolution>,\n  questContext?: QuestPromptContext,\n  hitlMode?: string\n): Promise<void> {\n  const { config, model } = opts;\n  const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n  const featureMap = new Map(features.map((f) => [f.id, f]));\n\n  // Show dashboard immediately\n  if (fmt === \"text\") printDashboard(state);\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773483652276,"end":1773483652283}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1773483652293,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdcf4bd001SeDVwKdElhabuf","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdcc6fc001v5dD7T26PPHtG4","type":"step-finish","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"b0b1e6e7096734b3e78498e02ca57dae03bf4ad2","cost":0,"tokens":{"total":103503,"input":25325,"output":353,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"read":77825,"write":0}}}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1773483656008,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdd0347001K9Rx788OoiUZVY","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdcf4d5001AAnA8255LQLtJd","type":"step-start","snapshot":"b0b1e6e7096734b3e78498e02ca57dae03bf4ad2"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483689130,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdd0347002TR20s10yZ2Yd47","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdcf4d5001AAnA8255LQLtJd","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement the \"Wave monitor quit should not stop running agents\" feature (Feature ID: `tui-background-wave`, branch: `feature/tui-background-wave`). This is an end-to-end verification of background wave support with three main deliverables:\n\n1. **Handle agents that finish while monitor is closed** — detect completion on next monitor open and update state/UI\n2. **Show a 'running wave detected' indicator in the Task Browser**\n3. **Edge cases**: all agents finish while closed, mixed success/failure while closed\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Use conventional commits with scope `tui-background-wave`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks` directory\n- Run `bun run build` to verify at the end\n- Use `portless run` for any server testing\n- Create a plan using TodoWrite tool before implementing\n\n## Discoveries\n\n### Current Architecture\n- **`src/commands/tui.ts`** is the main TUI orchestrator loop. It already detects running waves at the top of the loop (lines 122-133) and calls `cmdResume` to reconnect. When `cmdResume` returns (wave complete + user presses Q), it loops back to quest picker/browser.\n\n- **The critical problem**: Currently, pressing Q in the wave monitor calls `onQuit()` which calls `monitor.killAll()` and `process.exit(0)` — this **kills all agents**. Both `launch.ts` (line 1126-1129) and `resume.ts` (line 612-620) have this pattern. The quit handler needs to be changed so Q **detaches** from the monitor instead of killing agents.\n\n- **`src/lib/tui-browser.ts`** already has `setHasRunningWave(running: boolean)` method (line 421) and Tab key support for switching to monitor. BUT in `tui.ts`'s `showBrowser()` function (line 1004), `onSwitchToMonitor` is hardcoded to `undefined` — it's never wired up.\n\n- **`src/commands/resume.ts`** already has full agent recovery/triage logic (lines 161-260): it checks PIDs, detects dead processes with code changes, re-verifies builds, handles all terminal states. This is the mechanism that handles \"agents finished while monitor was closed.\"\n\n- **`src/lib/tui.ts`** (WomboTUI class): The `stop()` method only tears down the TUI screen — it does NOT kill agents. The `onQuit` callback is what kills agents. The key insight is that `stop()` is already safe for detach (it's used during mux attach/detach).\n\n- **State persistence**: `flushState()` and `saveState()` in `src/lib/state.ts` handle persisting wave state to `.wombo-combo/state.json`. The polling loop in both launch.ts and resume.ts periodically saves state.\n\n- **`WaveState` type** has agents with statuses: queued, installing, running, completed, verified, failed, merged, retry, resolving_conflict\n\n### Key Change Points Identified\n1. **`launch.ts` onQuit (line 1116-1130)**: Change from kill+exit to detach (save state, stop TUI, return to browser)\n2. **`resume.ts` onQuit (line 609-621)**: Same change — detach instead of kill+exit\n3. **`tui.ts` showBrowser (line 1004)**: Wire up `onSwitchToMonitor` callback\n4. **`tui.ts` main loop (lines 120-161)**: Already handles wave detection but could need refinement for the detach-and-return flow\n5. **Task Browser header/status**: May want to show a more prominent \"running wave\" indicator beyond just the Tab hint\n\n## Accomplished\n\n- **Read and analyzed all key source files** — full understanding of the architecture\n- **Identified all change points** needed for the feature\n- **No code changes made yet** — still in the analysis/planning phase\n- **No plan created yet** with TodoWrite tool\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Core files to modify:\n- `src/commands/tui.ts` — Main TUI orchestrator loop; needs `onSwitchToMonitor` wiring and detach flow\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — `launchWaveHeadless()` onQuit handler (line ~1116); gracefulShutdown handler (line ~1181); needs detach-friendly quit\n- `src/commands/resume.ts` — `cmdResume()` onQuit handler (line ~609); gracefulShutdown handler (line ~568); needs detach-friendly quit\n- `src/lib/tui.ts` — WomboTUI class; may need a `detach()` method or modified quit key behavior\n- `src/lib/tui-browser.ts` — TaskBrowser class; has `setHasRunningWave()`, header may need \"running wave\" indicator enhancement\n\n### Supporting files (read, understand context):\n- `src/lib/state.ts` — WaveState, AgentState types, loadState, saveState, flushState, isWaveComplete\n- `src/lib/monitor.ts` — ProcessMonitor class, manages agent processes\n- `src/lib/tui-quest-picker.ts` — QuestPicker class (may need running wave indicator too)\n- `src/lib/ui.ts` — Dashboard rendering helpers","time":{"start":1773483689128,"end":1773483689128}}}
