{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483737114,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebde3ee3001aBfFw0gVjeOnps","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebde35c60010b3o31UP0NOmtK","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_013Yr2ZhQJDz7iKDy2yz7Pbb","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/monitor.ts","limit":40,"offset":681},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/monitor.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>681:    * This is the primary teardown path. After killAll(), the parent\n682:    * process saves wave state and exits. Agents can be re-launched\n683:    * later via `woco resume`.\n684:    *\n685:    * Reconnected processes are NOT killed — they are independent agents\n686:    * (typically in mux sessions) that should survive the parent's exit.\n687:    * They are simply removed from the monitor map so polling stops.\n688:    */\n689:   killAll(): void {\n690:     for (const [id, m] of this.processes.entries()) {\n691:       if (m.reconnected) {\n692:         // Don't kill reconnected processes — just stop monitoring\n693:         this.processes.delete(id);\n694:       } else {\n695:         this.remove(id);\n696:       }\n697:     }\n698:   }\n699: \n700:   waitAll(pollIntervalMs: number = 1000): Promise<void> {\n701:     return new Promise((resolve) => {\n702:       const check = () => {\n703:         if (this.allDone()) {\n704:           resolve();\n705:         } else {\n706:           setTimeout(check, pollIntervalMs);\n707:         }\n708:       };\n709:       check();\n710:     });\n711:   }\n712: }\n713: \n714: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n715: // Re-exports from token-collector for convenience\n716: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n717: \n718: export { TokenCollector, type UsageRecord } from \"./token-collector.js\";\n719: export type { UsageSummary, UsageCallback } from \"./token-collector.js\";\n720: \n\n(Showing lines 681-720 of 726. Use offset=721 to continue.)\n</content>","title":"src/lib/monitor.ts","metadata":{"preview":"   * This is the primary teardown path. After killAll(), the parent\n   * process saves wave state and exits. Agents can be re-launched\n   * later via `woco resume`.\n   *\n   * Reconnected processes are NOT killed — they are independent agents\n   * (typically in mux sessions) that should survive the parent's exit.\n   * They are simply removed from the monitor map so polling stops.\n   */\n  killAll(): void {\n    for (const [id, m] of this.processes.entries()) {\n      if (m.reconnected) {\n        // Don't kill reconnected processes — just stop monitoring\n        this.processes.delete(id);\n      } else {\n        this.remove(id);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  waitAll(pollIntervalMs: number = 1000): Promise<void> {","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773483737112,"end":1773483737113}}}}
