{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1773483755830,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebde89350012K1SJrNTkkM4dO","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebde80df001fzlrmbk3TYMjwM","type":"step-start","snapshot":"b0b1e6e7096734b3e78498e02ca57dae03bf4ad2"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483766420,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebde8935002k35E1lxo1PYZnr","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebde80df001fzlrmbk3TYMjwM","type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding. Let me plan the implementation strategy:\n\n**The Core Problem:**\nWhen user presses Q in the wave monitor (WomboTUI), `onQuit()` is called which does `monitor.killAll()` + `process.exit(0)`. This kills all running agents.\n\n**The Solution:**\n1. In `launch.ts` and `resume.ts`, the `onQuit` callback should **NOT** kill agents or exit. Instead, it should:\n   - Save state to disk\n   - Stop the TUI (but not kill agents)\n   - Signal the monitoring loop to stop (so the function returns)\n   - The calling code in `tui.ts` then loops back to the browser\n\n2. We need a way to signal the monitoring `while (!isWaveComplete(state))` loop to exit early when the user presses Q. The simplest approach: a `detached` flag that the loop checks.\n\n3. The `gracefulShutdown` SIGINT/SIGTERM handlers should **still** kill agents (those are real process interrupts), but the Q key press should detach.\n\n4. In `tui.ts`, after `cmdLaunch` or `cmdResume` returns (whether because wave completed or because user detached), we already loop back to the browser. We just need the browser to show the running wave indicator and wire up `onSwitchToMonitor`.\n\nLet me start implementing. First, let me understand how `cmdLaunch` and `cmdResume` currently interact — do they use flags for TUI mode? Let me check `cmdResume` signature:","time":{"start":1773483766419,"end":1773483766419}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483766423,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdead4b0014MoKjP1w7UdOlC","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebde80df001fzlrmbk3TYMjwM","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_017EGN2kdQmqx6UdqXuAQpyx","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/resume.ts","limit":60,"offset":1},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/resume.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * resume.ts — Resume a previously stopped wave.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage: woco resume [options] [--output json]\n5:  *\n6:  * Restores from .wombo-combo/state.json:\n7:  *   - Agents in \"running\"/\"installing\" whose PID is dead → re-check or re-launch\n8:  *   - Agents in \"queued\" → launch them\n9:  *   - Agents in terminal states (verified/failed/merged) → leave alone\n10:  *\n11:  * ## Agent Recovery (audit: wave-detach-audit)\n12:  *\n13:  * This is the primary recovery mechanism for agents that died when the parent\n14:  * process was terminated (gracefully via SIGINT, or ungracefully via SIGKILL/crash).\n15:  *\n16:  * Recovery triage for each agent:\n17:  *   - PID still alive → leave it running (another wombo instance may still be active)\n18:  *   - PID dead + worktree has commits → run build verification on existing work\n19:  *   - PID dead + no commits → reset to \"queued\" for a fresh re-launch\n20:  *   - \"completed\" → verify build\n21:  *   - \"verified\" → attempt merge\n22:  *   - \"failed\" with retries remaining + worktree has commits → re-verify\n23:  *   - \"failed\" with retries remaining + no commits → re-launch\n24:  *   - \"failed\" with retries exhausted → leave alone (user can `woco retry`)\n25:  *\n26:  * This design means no agent work is permanently lost unless the worktree\n27:  * itself is destroyed (e.g., by `woco cleanup`).\n28:  */\n29: \n30: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n31: import type { Feature } from \"../lib/tasks.js\";\n32: import { loadFeatures } from \"../lib/tasks.js\";\n33: import {\n34:   loadState,\n35:   saveState,\n36:   flushState,\n37:   updateAgent,\n38:   queuedAgents,\n39:   readyToLaunchAgents,\n40:   cancelDownstream,\n41:   isWaveComplete,\n42:   type WaveState,\n43:   type AgentState,\n44: } from \"../lib/state.js\";\n45: import {\n46:   createWorktree,\n47:   installDeps,\n48:   worktreeReady,\n49:   worktreeExists,\n50:   branchHasChanges,\n51:   removeWorktree,\n52:   log as wtLog,\n53: } from \"../lib/worktree.js\";\n54: import { generatePrompt, type QuestPromptContext } from \"../lib/prompt.js\";\n55: import {\n56:   launchInteractive,\n57:   isProcessRunning,\n58:   getMultiplexerName,\n59: } from \"../lib/launcher.js\";\n60: import { ProcessMonitor } from \"../lib/monitor.js\";\n\n(Showing lines 1-60 of 789. Use offset=61 to continue.)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/resume.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * resume.ts — Resume a previously stopped wave.\n *\n * Usage: woco resume [options] [--output json]\n *\n * Restores from .wombo-combo/state.json:\n *   - Agents in \"running\"/\"installing\" whose PID is dead → re-check or re-launch\n *   - Agents in \"queued\" → launch them\n *   - Agents in terminal states (verified/failed/merged) → leave alone\n *\n * ## Agent Recovery (audit: wave-detach-audit)\n *\n * This is the primary recovery mechanism for agents that died when the parent\n * process was terminated (gracefully via SIGINT, or ungracefully via SIGKILL/crash).\n *\n * Recovery triage for each agent:\n *   - PID still alive → leave it running (another wombo instance may still be active)\n *   - PID dead + worktree has commits → run build verification on existing work\n *   - PID dead + no commits → reset to \"queued\" for a fresh re-launch\n *   - \"completed\" → verify build","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773483766418,"end":1773483766422}}}}
