{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483785650,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdecea9001EEqmPQ34QBIDjj","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdec6f7001hPn9dcHVsOluG7","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context I need. Let me implement the changes. The key insight is:\n\n**For `launch.ts` and `resume.ts`:**\n- The `onQuit` callback needs to be changed from \"kill agents + exit\" to \"detach\" mode\n- We need a flag (`detached`) that the monitoring loop can check to break out early\n- The `gracefulShutdown` for SIGINT/SIGTERM should still kill agents (those are real signals)\n- When called from `tui.ts` (the unified TUI), we want detach behavior. When called directly from CLI (`woco launch` / `woco resume`), we want the old kill behavior.\n\nThe cleanest approach: **Add an optional `onDetach` callback** to both `launchWaveHeadless` and `cmdResume` options. When `onQuit` fires from the TUI and `onDetach` is provided, call `onDetach` instead of killing agents. The monitoring loop checks a `detached` flag.\n\nActually, an even simpler approach: since `launch.ts` and `resume.ts` are called from `tui.ts`, and `tui.ts` catches the flow after they return, the simplest change is:\n\n1. Make the Q key in WomboTUI call `onQuit()` which now just stops the TUI and signals the poll loop to exit\n2. The poll loop exits, `launchWaveHeadless`/`cmdResume` returns normally\n3. Back in `tui.ts`, the loop continues to the browser\n\nBut wait — the SIGINT handlers also need to change conditionally. When running standalone (`woco launch`), SIGINT should kill agents. When running from `tui.ts`, it should detach.\n\nLet me look at how `cmdLaunch` calls `launchWaveHeadless`:","time":{"start":1773483785649,"end":1773483785649}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483785653,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdefa5b001tTPStGqqieTPCV","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdec6f7001hPn9dcHVsOluG7","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_011gLZzakq9MTrsqn37UJr4B","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts","limit":80,"offset":1533},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1533: export async function cmdLaunch(opts: LaunchCommandOptions): Promise<void> {\n1534:   const { projectRoot } = opts;\n1535:   let { config } = opts;\n1536:   const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n1537: \n1538:   if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(\"\\n--- wombo-combo: Launch ---\\n\");\n1539: \n1540:   // Ensure agent definition exists — reinstall from template if missing\n1541:   ensureAgentDefinition(projectRoot, config, opts.agent);\n1542: \n1543:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1544:   // Quest resolution — if --quest was specified, scope the wave to that quest\n1545:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1546:   let questContext: QuestPromptContext | undefined;\n1547:   let questId: string | null = opts.questId ?? null;\n1548: \n1549:   if (questId) {\n1550:     const quest = loadQuest(projectRoot, questId);\n1551:     if (!quest) {\n1552:       outputError(fmt, `Quest \"${questId}\" not found. Use 'woco quest list' to see available quests.`);\n1553:       return; // unreachable\n1554:     }\n1555: \n1556:     if (quest.status !== \"active\") {\n1557:       outputError(fmt, `Quest \"${questId}\" is in status \"${quest.status}\" — only active quests can be launched. Use 'woco quest activate ${questId}' first.`);\n1558:       return; // unreachable\n1559:     }\n1560: \n1561:     // Ensure the quest branch exists (create from baseBranch if needed)\n1562:     if (!questBranchExists(projectRoot, questId)) {\n1563:       if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`Creating quest branch \"${quest.branch}\" from \"${quest.baseBranch}\"...`);\n1564:       createQuestBranch(projectRoot, questId, quest.baseBranch);\n1565:     }\n1566: \n1567:     // Override baseBranch — task branches will fork from the quest branch\n1568:     opts.baseBranch = quest.branch;\n1569:     if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1570:       console.log(`Quest: ${quest.title} (${questId})`);\n1571:       console.log(`  Base branch overridden to: ${quest.branch}`);\n1572:     }\n1573: \n1574:     // Apply quest config overrides (layered on top of project config)\n1575:     config = resolveQuestConfig(config, quest);\n1576: \n1577:     // Build quest prompt context for agent prompts\n1578:     const knowledge = loadQuestKnowledge(projectRoot, questId);\n1579:     questContext = {\n1580:       questId: quest.id,\n1581:       goal: quest.goal,\n1582:       addedConstraints: quest.constraints.add ?? [],\n1583:       addedForbidden: quest.constraints.ban ?? [],\n1584:       knowledge,\n1585:     };\n1586: \n1587:     if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1588:       const constraintCount = questContext.addedConstraints.length + questContext.addedForbidden.length;\n1589:       if (constraintCount > 0) {\n1590:         console.log(`  Quest constraints: ${questContext.addedConstraints.length} added, ${questContext.addedForbidden.length} banned`);\n1591:       }\n1592:       if (knowledge) {\n1593:         console.log(`  Quest knowledge: loaded (${knowledge.length} bytes)`);\n1594:       }\n1595:       console.log(\"\");\n1596:     }\n1597:   }\n1598: \n1599:   // Extract HITL mode from quest (defaults to undefined / yolo for non-quest waves)\n1600:   const hitlMode = questId ? loadQuest(projectRoot, questId)?.hitlMode : undefined;\n1601: \n1602:   // Ensure portless proxy is running (if enabled) to prevent port collisions\n1603:   if (config.portless.enabled) {\n1604:     if (isPortlessAvailable(config)) {\n1605:       const proxyOk = ensureProxyRunning(config);\n1606:       if (!proxyOk && fmt === \"text\") {\n1607:         console.warn(\n1608:           \"\\x1b[33m[portless]\\x1b[0m proxy could not be started — agents may encounter port collisions\"\n1609:         );\n1610:       }\n1611:     } else if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1612:       console.warn(\n\n(Showing lines 1533-1612 of 1950. Use offset=1613 to continue.)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/launch.ts","metadata":{"preview":"export async function cmdLaunch(opts: LaunchCommandOptions): Promise<void> {\n  const { projectRoot } = opts;\n  let { config } = opts;\n  const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n\n  if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(\"\\n--- wombo-combo: Launch ---\\n\");\n\n  // Ensure agent definition exists — reinstall from template if missing\n  ensureAgentDefinition(projectRoot, config, opts.agent);\n\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // Quest resolution — if --quest was specified, scope the wave to that quest\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  let questContext: QuestPromptContext | undefined;\n  let questId: string | null = opts.questId ?? null;\n\n  if (questId) {\n    const quest = loadQuest(projectRoot, questId);\n    if (!quest) {\n      outputError(fmt, `Quest \"${questId}\" not found. Use 'woco quest list' to see available quests.`);","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773483785648,"end":1773483785652}}}}
