{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1773483794675,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdf20f2001dngBstWxm4HEtg","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdf19b30015z2Fx1S0QPs2Wq","type":"step-start","snapshot":"b0b1e6e7096734b3e78498e02ca57dae03bf4ad2"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483817159,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdf20f3001a8XGeHF9Wls9GZ","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdf19b30015z2Fx1S0QPs2Wq","type":"text","text":"Now I see the full picture. `cmdLaunch` calls `launchWaveHeadless` which contains both the TUI setup AND the monitoring loop. The `process.exit(0)` in `onQuit` means the function never returns normally when Q is pressed — it just kills the process.\n\nMy approach:\n1. In `launchWaveHeadless`, change `onQuit` from \"kill all + exit\" to \"set detached flag + stop TUI\" \n2. Add a `detached` flag that the monitoring loop checks alongside `isWaveComplete`\n3. When detached, DON'T kill agents, DON'T call `process.exit(0)` — just break from the loop and return\n4. Same change in `cmdResume`\n5. The `gracefulShutdown` for SIGINT/SIGTERM should still kill agents when running standalone, but when running from TUI, it should detach instead. However, for simplicity and safety, let's keep SIGINT/SIGTERM killing agents always — the Q key behavior is what we're changing.\n\nWait, actually let me reconsider. When running inside `cmdTui`, SIGINT should probably also not kill agents — the user might just be trying to exit the TUI. But that's more complex. Let me focus on the Q key behavior first and keep SIGINT behavior the same for now.\n\nActually, re-reading the task description: \"Wave monitor quit should not stop running agents\". This is specifically about the Q key in the monitor. SIGINT is a separate concern. Let's focus on Q.\n\nThe key change is: `onQuit` should NOT call `monitor.killAll()` or `process.exit(0)`. Instead, it should save state and signal the monitoring loop to exit normally.\n\nLet me implement this now:","time":{"start":1773483817159,"end":1773483817159}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483817793,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebdf4b5e001OyiQUpyNM6FjFY","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebdf19b30015z2Fx1S0QPs2Wq","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01A8e1gsWbLXLYLtzhKyvNRz","tool":"edit","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts","oldString":"  // Create the TUI — it will auto-refresh and show activity from the monitor\n  const tuiRef = { current: null as WomboTUI | null };\n  const startTUI = () => {\n    tuiRef.current = new WomboTUI({\n      state,\n      monitor,\n      projectRoot,\n      interactive: false,\n      config,\n      onQuit: () => {\n          // Audit (wave-detach-audit): This is the TUI quit path — equivalent\n          // to the SIGINT handler. Kills all agents, saves state, and exits.\n          // Agents are non-detached children, so they die when we exit anyway,\n          // but explicit killAll() gives them SIGTERM for graceful shutdown.\n          for (const agent of state.agents) {\n            if (agent.status === \"running\" || agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") {\n            updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, { activity: \"interrupted\" });\n          }\n        }\n        monitor.killAll();\n        flushState(projectRoot, state);\n        if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(\"State saved. Use 'woco resume' to continue.\");\n        process.exit(0);\n      },","newString":"  // Create the TUI — it will auto-refresh and show activity from the monitor\n  //\n  // Detach support: When the user presses Q in the monitor TUI, we no longer\n  // kill agents and exit. Instead, we set a `detached` flag and let the\n  // monitoring loop exit naturally. The caller (cmdTui) then loops back to\n  // the task browser, which shows a \"running wave\" indicator.\n  let detached = false;\n  const tuiRef = { current: null as WomboTUI | null };\n  const startTUI = () => {\n    tuiRef.current = new WomboTUI({\n      state,\n      monitor,\n      projectRoot,\n      interactive: false,\n      config,\n      onQuit: () => {\n          // Detach from the wave monitor — agents keep running in the background.\n          // The monitoring loop checks `detached` and exits, returning control\n          // to the caller (cmdTui main loop or cmdLaunch).\n          flushState(projectRoot, state);\n          detached = true;\n      },"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","title":"src/commands/launch.ts","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/tui.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":29,"character":0},"end":{"line":29,"character":46}},"message":"'execSync' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"}],"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":33,"character":2},"end":{"line":33,"character":19}},"message":"'areAgentDepsReady' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":7},"end":{"line":38,"character":29}},"message":"'SerializedSchedulePlan' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":57,"character":2},"end":{"line":57,"character":18}},"message":"'retryInteractive' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":78,"character":7},"end":{"line":78,"character":15}},"message":"'DepGraph' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":81,"character":50},"end":{"line":81,"character":61}},"message":"'portlessUrl' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":104,"character":76},"end":{"line