{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483901686,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe095bf0016f0H9UISXDcgzE","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe08d12001GvdkTgWfDMVoWd","type":"text","text":"Actually wait — looking at the WomboTUI key handler again:\n\n```typescript\nthis.screen.key([\"q\", \"C-c\"], () => {\n  this.stop();  // <-- This already stops the TUI\n  if (this.waveComplete && this.waveCompleteResolve) {\n    this.waveCompleteResolve();\n  } else {\n    this.onQuit();  // <-- This is our callback\n  }\n});\n```\n\nThe `this.stop()` call already destroys the screen. So when `onQuit()` is called, the TUI is already stopped. We just need to null out the ref in the monitoring loop context. But `tuiRef.current` is checked by the monitoring loop, and after `stop()`, the TUI instance still exists but its screen is destroyed. The `updateState` call would just set a property on a defunct object — harmless but wasteful.\n\nLet me set `tuiRef.current = null` in the onQuit callback to ensure the monitoring loop stops trying to interact with the destroyed TUI. Actually no — the `onQuit` is a closure inside the WomboTUI constructor, it doesn't have access to `tuiRef`. But it does via the closure over the outer function scope.\n\nWait, let me re-read: the `onQuit` callback is defined inside `startTUI()` which is inside `launchWaveHeadless()` — and `tuiRef` is also in `launchWaveHeadless()`. So the closure does have access.\n\nBut actually, the `onQuit` is called from inside WomboTUI's key handler, AFTER `this.stop()` is already called. So the TUI is already stopped. I should null out `tuiRef.current` in the onQuit callback to prevent the monitoring loop from trying to interact with a destroyed TUI during the remaining poll iterations:","time":{"start":1773483901685,"end":1773483901685}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483902271,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe0b824001OxpeeuiGNkIgAO","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe08d12001GvdkTgWfDMVoWd","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01EWAsgXetRMygRmc6q8iK22","tool":"edit","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts","newString":"      onQuit: () => {\n          // Detach from the wave monitor — agents keep running in the background.\n          // The monitoring loop checks `detached` and exits, returning control\n          // to the caller (cmdTui main loop or cmdLaunch).\n          flushState(projectRoot, state);\n          // Null out the TUI ref so the monitoring loop stops trying to update\n          // the destroyed screen during remaining poll iterations.\n          tuiRef.current = null;\n          detached = true;\n      },","oldString":"      onQuit: () => {\n          // Detach from the wave monitor — agents keep running in the background.\n          // The monitoring loop checks `detached` and exits, returning control\n          // to the caller (cmdTui main loop or cmdLaunch).\n          flushState(projectRoot, state);\n          detached = true;\n      },"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","title":"src/commands/launch.ts","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/tui.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":29,"character":0},"end":{"line":29,"character":46}},"message":"'execSync' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"}],"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":33,"character":2},"end":{"line":33,"character":19}},"message":"'areAgentDepsReady' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":