{"type":"text","timestamp":1773484083745,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe37357002SUxDD1U8x2xaAm","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe36b1c001bF2Q9l76T4e73e","type":"text","text":"Now let me handle the edge cases. The key edge cases are:\n\n1. **All agents finish while monitor is closed** — when the user presses Tab to switch back to the monitor, `cmdResume` will detect all agents are in terminal states and the wave is complete. It should handle this gracefully.\n\n2. **Mixed success/failure while closed** — same as above, `cmdResume`'s triage logic handles this already (lines 161-260 in resume.ts).\n\nLet me verify that `cmdResume` handles these correctly. When the user presses Tab to switch to the monitor, `cmdResume` is called. The triage logic at the top of `cmdResume` will:\n- Detect dead PIDs\n- Re-verify completed agents\n- Mark failed agents appropriately\n- If all agents are done → `isWaveComplete(state)` returns true → monitoring loop exits immediately → post-wave cleanup runs\n\nLet me verify the wave completion check in `isWaveComplete`:","time":{"start":1773484083744,"end":1773484083744}}}
