{"type":"text","timestamp":1773484176534,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe4ea8b002FIZpZ15ZPxKfUU","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe4e25000179JvI2Qiw62rZn","type":"text","text":"Good — the SIGINT/SIGTERM handler in `launch.ts` still kills agents and exits. This is correct: SIGINT means the user pressed Ctrl+C, which is a hard stop. Only the Q key (via `onQuit`) detaches without killing.\n\nLet me now verify the resume.ts graceful shutdown handler:","time":{"start":1773484176534,"end":1773484176534}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773484176539,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe4f285001nOCA04u7ngjvFf","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe4e25000179JvI2Qiw62rZn","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01DwK5cB5dnqTrAqBVz6cFg7","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/resume.ts","limit":25,"offset":563},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/resume.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>563:     // Handle graceful shutdown\n564:     // Audit (wave-detach-audit): Same pattern as launch.ts — see launch.ts\n565:     // SIGINT handler for detailed lifecycle documentation. Agents are\n566:     // non-detached children; killAll() gives them SIGTERM before exit.\n567:     let detached = false;\n568:     const tuiRef = { current: null as WomboTUI | null };\n569:     const gracefulShutdown = (signal: string) => {\n570:       if (tuiRef.current) tuiRef.current.stop();\n571:       for (const agent of state.agents) {\n572:         if (agent.status === \"running\" || agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") {\n573:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n574:             activity: \"interrupted\",\n575:           });\n576:         }\n577:       }\n578:       monitor.killAll();\n579:       flushState(projectRoot, state);\n580:       if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`\\nState saved (${signal}). Use 'woco resume' to continue.`);\n581:       process.exit(0);\n582:     };\n583:     process.on(\"SIGINT\", () => gracefulShutdown(\"SIGINT\"));\n584:     process.on(\"SIGTERM\", () => gracefulShutdown(\"SIGTERM\"));\n585:     process.on(\"SIGHUP\", () => gracefulShutdown(\"SIGHUP\"));\n586: \n587:     // Reconnect to agents that are still alive — register them in the monitor\n\n(Showing lines 563-587 of 795. Use offset=588 to continue.)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/resume.ts","metadata":{"preview":"    // Handle graceful shutdown\n    // Audit (wave-detach-audit): Same pattern as launch.ts — see launch.ts\n    // SIGINT handler for detailed lifecycle documentation. Agents are\n    // non-detached children; killAll() gives them SIGTERM before exit.\n    let detached = false;\n    const tuiRef = { current: null as WomboTUI | null };\n    const gracefulShutdown = (signal: string) => {\n      if (tuiRef.current) tuiRef.current.stop();\n      for (const agent of state.agents) {\n        if (agent.status === \"running\" || agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") {\n          updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n            activity: \"interrupted\",\n          });\n        }\n      }\n      monitor.killAll();\n      flushState(projectRoot, state);\n      if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`\\nState saved (${signal}). Use 'woco resume' to continue.`);\n      process.exit(0);\n    };","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773484176533,"end":1773484176538}}}}
