{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773484210404,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe57686001JrCKgtFhcaeK6f","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe5390d001dmWM2Faw7S3iil","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01BtejZvQHzAyuFLGF8ZPSKz","tool":"grep","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"include":"src/lib/launcher.ts","pattern":"\\.unref\\(\\)|detached"},"output":"Found 10 matches\n/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/launcher.ts:\n  Line 16:  *   - Agents are spawned with `detached: false` — they are child processes of\n  Line 36:  * **Design rationale for `detached: false`**:\n  Line 39:  *   tracking). Using `detached: true` + `unref()` would allow agents to\n  Line 171:  * The child process is spawned with `detached: false` — it is tied to the\n  Line 195:     detached: false,\n  Line 211:  * Same lifecycle as `launchHeadless` — spawned with `detached: false`,\n  Line 235:     detached: false,\n  Line 273:  * Same lifecycle as `launchHeadless` — spawned with `detached: false`,\n  Line 300:     detached: false,\n  Line 359:   // Create a detached session running the agent","title":"\\.unref\\(\\)|detached","metadata":{"matches":10,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1773484210400,"end":1773484210404}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773484210414,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe54357001x4dS6GLVhI4oAt","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe5390d001dmWM2Faw7S3iil","type":"text","text":"OK. When `cmdLaunch` or `cmdResume` returns normally (after detach), the switch case falls through to `break`, and the process exits naturally. This is fine — the user ran `woco launch`, the agents are running, and the process exits cleanly. The agents continue as child processes... wait, no. If the parent process exits, the child processes would be killed because they're non-detached.\n\nThis is the critical issue! When running standalone `woco launch` (not through `cmdTui`), pressing Q would:\n1. Set `detached = true` (but not kill agents)\n2. The monitoring loop exits\n3. The function returns\n4. The `index.ts` switch case completes\n5. The process exits\n6. All child processes (agents) are killed by the OS because they're non-detached!\n\nSo the detach behavior is only useful when running through `cmdTui`, where the main loop stays alive. For standalone `woco launch`, the Q key detach would effectively kill the agents because the process exits.\n\nHowever, looking more carefully at the `gracefulShutdown` handler: it has `process.exit(0)`. The SIGINT handler would fire when the process is about to exit naturally... actually no. The process exits naturally after `cmdLaunch` returns and the switch falls through to `break`. There's no explicit `process.exit()` — the process just exits when the event loop drains.\n\nBut with our changes, after detach:\n1. `launchWaveHeadless` returns\n2. `cmdLaunch` returns  \n3. Control goes back to `index.ts`\n4. The switch case completes\n5. The event loop has nothing to do (except the child process event listeners and possibly the ProcessMonitor polling)\n6. The child processes keep the event loop alive!\n\nActually, the ChildProcess objects keep the event loop alive because they have 'exit' event listeners. The process won't exit until all child processes are done. And the `isProcessRunning()` polling intervals in the ProcessMonitor (for reconnected processes) also keep the event loop alive (unless `.unref()` is called).\n\nLet me check if the ChildProcess objects have `.unref()`:","time":{"start":1773484210413,"end":1773484210413}}}
