{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773484226000,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe5b4f1001oacY6KfTtbAx0f","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe57910001Lp6Vwrz3AW7lx5","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01KR2E3yLoS2AMecrryJn28u","tool":"grep","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"include":"src/commands/launch.ts","pattern":"export interface LaunchCommandOptions"},"output":"Found 1 matches\n/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts:\n  Line 146: export interface LaunchCommandOptions {","title":"export interface LaunchCommandOptions","metadata":{"matches":1,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1773484225996,"end":1773484225999}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773484226003,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe584250020rKX0S1a6KG2yo","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe57910001Lp6Vwrz3AW7lx5","type":"text","text":"OK, so agents are spawned with `detached: false` and no `.unref()`. This means the ChildProcess objects keep the parent event loop alive. So when `launchWaveHeadless` returns after detach, the parent process will NOT exit immediately — it will stay alive until all child processes exit.\n\nBut the user just pressed Q to exit the monitor — they expect the terminal to be available for other things. The process is now running in the background with no TUI, no output, just waiting for child processes to finish. This is actually the correct behavior for \"detach\" — the process stays alive but the monitor is closed.\n\nHowever, for standalone `woco launch`, this might be confusing — the user presses Q and the process doesn't exit. Let me consider adding a message:\n\nActually wait, for standalone `woco launch`, after `launchWaveHeadless` returns, `cmdLaunch` returns, and `index.ts` reaches the `break`. The event loop will then be held alive by the child processes. But there's no user feedback about what's happening.\n\nFor the TUI flow (through `cmdTui`), this doesn't matter because the main loop continues to show the browser. The child processes keep the event loop alive, which is what we want.\n\nFor standalone, let me add a message in `launchWaveHeadless` after the detach return:\n\nActually, let me re-read what happens after the detach return in `launchWaveHeadless`:\n\n```typescript\nif (detached) {\n    flushState(projectRoot, state);\n    return;\n}\n```\n\nThe function returns. In `cmdLaunch`, there's no special handling after `launchWaveHeadless` returns — it just returns void. Then in `index.ts`, the `break` is reached. The process stays alive because of child processes.\n\nThe user pressed Q and now sees a terminal prompt but the process is still running in the background. They can't do `woco resume` in the same terminal because it would start a second woco process.\n\nFor standalone `woco launch`/`woco resume`, the old behavior (kill agents and exit) was actually more appropriate. Let me consider making the behavior conditional:\n\n- When called from `cmdTui` → detach (don't kill agents)\n- When called standalone → kill agents and exit (old behavior)\n\nThe simplest way: pass a flag indicating whether detach is supported. Let me think about the API...\n\nActually, looking at the `LaunchCommandOptions`:","time":{"start":1773484226003,"end":1773484226003}}}
