{"type":"text","timestamp":1773484433389,"sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","part":{"id":"prt_cebe8c1c1002GkCBsEC9a95bXZ","sessionID":"ses_31423da25ffebo9V1CTFH0IpgT","messageID":"msg_cebe8b63d001PP0oZndTd9fsd7","type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of what was completed:\n\n## Completed\n\nAll remaining work items have been implemented and committed:\n\n1. **Fixed `resume.ts` `onQuit` handler** — Added the conditional `detachOnQuit` check (same pattern as `launch.ts`). When `detachOnQuit: true`, it detaches and returns to caller. When `false`/`undefined` (standalone `woco resume`), it kills agents and calls `process.exit(0)`.\n\n2. **Passed `detachOnQuit: true` in all 3 calls from `tui.ts`:**\n   - Auto-resume at top of loop (line ~153)\n   - \"monitor\" action handler (Tab key from browser, line ~273)\n   - \"launch\" action handler (cmdLaunch call, line ~320)\n\n3. **Typecheck passes** ✅\n4. **Build passes** ✅ (1.32 MB bundle, 179 modules)\n5. **Committed** as `ba4e0bf` on `feature/tui-background-wave`\n\nThe feature is now complete. The full behavior:\n- **TUI users** (`woco` / `cmdTui`): Q detaches from monitor → returns to browser → shows ⚡ WAVE RUNNING badge → Tab switches back to monitor\n- **Standalone users** (`woco launch` / `woco resume`): Q kills agents and exits (preserving original behavior)\n- **Anti-loop**: `skipAutoResume` flag prevents auto-resume loop after explicit detach","time":{"start":1773484433388,"end":1773484433388}}}
